{"title":"VPBROADCAST â€” Load Integer and Broadcast","fields":[{"name":"Instruction Modes","value":"`VPBROADCASTB xmm1, xmm2/m8`\n`VPBROADCASTB ymm1, xmm2/m8`\n`VPBROADCASTB xmm1{k1}{z}, xmm2/m8`\n`VPBROADCASTB ymm1{k1}{z}, xmm2/m8`\n`VPBROADCASTB zmm1{k1}{z}, xmm2/m8`\n`VPBROADCASTW xmm1, xmm2/m16`\n`VPBROADCASTW ymm1, xmm2/m16`\n`VPBROADCASTW xmm1{k1}{z}, xmm2/m16`\n`VPBROADCASTW ymm1{k1}{z}, xmm2/m16`\n`VPBROADCASTW zmm1{k1}{z}, xmm2/m16`\n`VPBROADCASTD xmm1, xmm2/m32`\n`VPBROADCASTD ymm1, xmm2/m32`\n`VPBROADCASTD xmm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m32`\n`VPBROADCASTD ymm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m32`\n`VPBROADCASTD zmm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m32`\n`VPBROADCASTQ xmm1, xmm2/m64`\n`VPBROADCASTQ ymm1, xmm2/m64`\n`VPBROADCASTQ xmm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m64`\n`VPBROADCASTQ ymm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m64`\n`VPBROADCASTQ zmm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m64`\n`VBROADCASTI32x2 xmm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m64`\n`VBROADCASTI32x2 ymm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m64`\n`VBROADCASTI32x2 zmm1 {k1}{z}, xmm2/m64`\n`VBROADCASTI128 ymm1, m128`\n`VBROADCASTI32X4 ymm1 {k1}{z}, m128`\n`VBROADCASTI32X4 zmm1 {k1}{z}, m128`\n`VBROADCASTI64X2 ymm1 {k1}{z}, m128`\n`VBROADCASTI64X2 zmm1 {k1}{z}, m128`\n`VBROADCASTI32X8 zmm1 {k1}{z}, m256`\n`VBROADCASTI64X4 zmm1 {k1}{z}, m256`"},{"name":"Description","value":"Load integer data from the source operand (the second operand) and broadcast to all elements of the destination operand (the first operand)."},{"name":"\u200b","value":"VEX256-encoded VPBROADCASTB/W/D/Q: The source operand is 8-bit, 16-bit, 32-bit, 64-bit memory location or the low 8-bit, 16-bit 32-bit, 64-bit data in an XMM register. The destination operand is a YMM register. VPBROADCASTI128 support the source operand of 128-bit memory location. Register source encodings for VPBROADCASTI128 is reserved and will #UD. Bits (MAXVL-1:256) of the destination register are zeroed."},{"name":"\u200b","value":"EVEX-encoded VPBROADCASTD/Q: The source operand is a 32-bit, 64-bit memory location or the low 32-bit, 64-bit data in an XMM register. The destination operand is a ZMM/YMM/XMM register and updated according to the writemask k1."},{"name":"\u200b","value":"VPBROADCASTI32X4 and VPBROADCASTI64X4: The destination operand is a ZMM register and updated according to the writemask k1. The source operand is 128-bit or 256-bit memory location. Register source encodings for VBROADCASTI32X4 and VBROADCASTI64X4 are reserved and will #UD."},{"name":"\u200b","value":"Note: VEX.vvvv and EVEX.vvvv are reserved and must be 1111b otherwise instructions will #UD."},{"name":"\u200b","value":"If VPBROADCASTI128 is encoded with VEX.L= 0, an attempt to execute the instruction encoded with VEX.L= 0 will cause an #UD exception."},{"name":"C/C++ Intriniscs","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m512i _mm512_broadcastb_epi8( __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m512i _mm512_mask_broadcastb_epi8(__m512i s, __mmask64 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m512i _mm512_maskz_broadcastb_epi8( __mmask64 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m256i _mm256_broadcastb_epi8(__m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m256i _mm256_mask_broadcastb_epi8(__m256i s, __mmask32 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m256i _mm256_maskz_broadcastb_epi8( __mmask32 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m128i _mm_mask_broadcastb_epi8(__m128i s, __mmask16 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m128i _mm_maskz_broadcastb_epi8( __mmask16 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTB __m128i _mm_broadcastb_epi8(__m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTD __m512i _mm512_broadcastd_epi32( __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTD __m512i _mm512_mask_broadcastd_epi32(__m512i s, __mmask16 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTD __m512i _mm512_maskz_broadcastd_epi32( __mmask16 k, __m128i a);\n`"},{"name":"\u200b","value":"`VPBROADCASTD __m256i _mm256_broadcastd_epi32( __m128i a);\n`"},{"nam